        "executive_summary": "AON's two clinics show divergent trajectories in March 2026. INHAR Harcourt delivered strong operational gains, with scheduler compliance rising from 63.5% in February to 72.4% in March and treatments running past closing declining from 4.0 daily to 2.8 daily, though its performance score of 45 out of 100 (where 50 represents the network average) reflects persistent overbooking at 110.7% chair utilization. GAMCN CGCC Macon improved scheduler compliance from 78.5% in February to 85.7% in March and nurse utilization from 48.8% in February to 55.7% in March, yet patient delays of 38.4 minutes remain 64% above the company average of 23.39 minutes, and treatments past closing worsened from 3.8 daily to 5.4 daily.",
        "highlights": [
          "INHAR Harcourt achieved a 30.4% reduction in daily treatments running past closing, dropping from 4.0 in February to 2.8 in March, alongside a 26.7% reduction in minutes per patient past close from 27.1 in February to 19.9 in March\u2014meaningful gains in schedule adherence. Both clinics strengthened scheduler compliance: INHAR Harcourt advanced 14.0 percentage points from 63.5% in February to 72.4% in March, while GAMCN CGCC Macon gained 9.3 percentage points from 78.5% in February to 85.7% in March, outpacing the company average of 81.42%."
